able input and output formats for subtasks.\\\",\\n    \\\"Establish naming conventions for subtasks.\\\",\\n    \\\"Set standards for subtask descriptions to ensure clarity.\\\",\\n    \\\"Define error handling procedures for subtasks.\\\",\\n    \\\"Determine the level of detail required in subtask documentation.\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The current list outlines steps to create criteria rather than the criteria themselves.  \\n- The task requires explicit definitions of what makes a subtask both “atomic” and “executable.”  \\n- We need concise, actionable criteria—each item should be a standalone rule that can be applied directly.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Single responsibility: each subtask performs exactly one well-defined action\\\",\\n    \\\"Independence: subtask can run without requiring other subtasks to complete first\\\",\\n    \\\"Clear inputs: all required inputs are explicitly defined and minimal\\\",\\n    \\\"Explicit outputs: result or side effects are clearly specified and measurable\\\",\\n    \\\"Determinism: same inputs always produce the same outputs\\\",\\n    \\\"Automatability: the subtask can be executed by a machine without manual intervention\\\",\\n    \\\"Minimal scope: contains only the essential steps needed to achieve its goal\\\",\\n    \\\"Error handling: specifies how failures are detected and reported\\\",\\n    \\\"Repeatability: can be run multiple times with consistent behavior\\\",\\n    \\\"Standardized naming: uses a clear, consistent naming convention for easy identification\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\n\\nYour task is to:\\n- Analyze a user objective\\n- Break it into atomic executable subtasks\\n- Each subtask should represent ONE specialized operation\\n- Keep subtasks concise and action-oriented\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\nExample:\\n[\\n    \\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n]\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Decompose each actionable component into specialized atomic subtasks\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDefine criteria for what constitutes an atomic executable subtask\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Atomic: Performs a single, indivisible action.\\\",\\n    \\\"Executable: Can be run independently with defined inputs and outputs.\\\",\\n    \\\"Specialized: Focuses on one specific operation.\\\",\\n    \\\"Concise: Achieves its goal with minimal steps.\\\",\\n    \\\"Independent: Does not rely on the completion of other subtasks to start.\\\",\\n    \\\"Testable: Output can be easily verified.\\\",\\n    \\\"Documented: Purpose and usage are clearly described.\\\",\\n    \\\"Idempotent: Repeated execution produces the same result if the state hasn't changed.\\\",\\n    \\\"Autonomous: Requires no manual intervention during execution.\\\",\\n    \\\"Unambiguous: Has a clear and well-defined purpose.\\\"\\n]\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:29:54.862271\"\n}"}
