\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The subtasks provided are meta-steps about how to decompose an objective, rather than the actionable components derived from the specific high-level objective (“You are a workflow planning agent”).\\n- Each subtask should directly represent a core action that the agent will perform in planning a workflow.\\n- The list should outline the actual steps the agent will take, not the process of breaking them down.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n[\\n    \\\"Gather the user's workflow planning objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze workflow requirements and constraints\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify major workflow phases\\\",\\n    \\\"Decompose each phase into atomic tasks\\\",\\n    \\\"Sequence tasks in logical order\\\",\\n    \\\"Validate task dependencies and completeness\\\"\\n]\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 1\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Understand user's objective and desired outcome\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify key steps required to achieve the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Define inputs and outputs for each step\\\",\\n    \\\"Determine the dependencies between steps\\\",\\n    \\\"Outline the resources needed for each step\\\",\\n    \\\"Estimate the time and effort required for each step\\\",\\n    \\\"Prioritize and sequence the steps in a logical order\\\",\\n    \\\"Document the workflow plan for execution\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 1\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The second subtask (“Identify key steps required to achieve the objective”) is still a meta-planning instruction rather than an actual step the agent will perform.\\n- We should turn each item into a concrete, single-action operation that the workflow planning agent will execute.\\n- Include a validation/review step to ensure completeness and readiness for execution.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n[\\n    \\\"Gather the user's high-level workflow objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the objective to identify major workflow phases\\\",\\n    \\\"Break each phase into atomic, actionable tasks\\\",\\n    \\\"Define inputs and outputs for every task\\\",\\n    \\\"Determine dependencies and logical sequencing of tasks\\\",\\n    \\\"Estimate required time, effort, and resources per task\\\",\\n    \\\"Review and validate the workflow plan for completeness\\\",\\n    \\\"Document the finalized workflow plan for execution\\\"\\n]\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 2\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Receive high-level objective from the user\\\",\\n    \\\"Clarify ambiguous aspects of the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Deconstruct the objective into major milestones\\\",\\n    \\\"Transform milestones into concrete actions\\\",\\n    \\\"Refine actions into specialized subtasks\\\",\\n    \\\"Ensure each subtask is independently executable\\\",\\n    \\\"Prioritize subtasks based on dependencies and urgency\\\",\\n    \\\"Present the list of actionable subtasks\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 2\\n## FEEDBACK to Current Result\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The subtasks remain high-level meta-instructions about planning rather than distinct, single-action operations the agent will perform.\\n- Steps like “Clarify ambiguous aspects” bundle multiple actions (identifying ambiguities and asking for clarification) into one.\\n- We need explicit, concrete actions (e.g., detect ambiguities, send clarification questions) and ensure each item is one atomic operation.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Receive and read the user's high-level objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify ambiguous or undefined terms in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate and send questions to clarify ambiguities\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract major milestones from the clarified objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Decompose each milestone into atomic tasks\\\",\\n    \\\"Specify the input and output for each task\\\",\\n    \\\"Determine dependencies and sequence tasks logically\\\",\\n    \\\"Present the final list of executable subtasks\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## VERSION 3\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Receive and interpret the user's objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify the desired outcome of the workflow\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract key entities and resources involved\\\",\\n    \\\"Detect implicit assumptions and constraints\\\",\\n    \\\"Define the scope and boundaries of the workflow\\\",\\n    \\\"Outline the major phases of the workflow\\\",\\n    \\\"Prioritize phases based on dependencies and impact\\\",\\n    \\\"Confirm understanding of the objective and constraints\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 3\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- Some items combine multiple operations (e.g., “Extract key entities and resources” should be two separate actions).\\n- “Receive and interpret” bundles two steps; interpret should follow receipt.\\n- “Detect implicit assumptions and constraints” mixes two different identification tasks.\\n- “Confirm understanding” is vague; better to explicitly generate clarification questions for any ambiguities.\\n- Each subtask must represent one very specific, atomic action.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Receive the user's high-level objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Interpret the objective details\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify the desired workflow outcome\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract key entities mentioned in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract required resources specified by the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Detect implicit assumptions in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify explicit constraints in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Define the workflow's scope\\\",\\n    \\\"Outline the workflow's boundaries\\\",\\n    \\\"Outline major workflow phases\\\",\\n    \\\"Prioritize each phase based on dependencies\\\",\\n    \\\"Sequence phases in logical order\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate and send clarification questions for ambiguities\\\"\\n]\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"user\",\n      \"content\": \"# **The Overall Goal**\\nYou are a workflow planning agent.\\n\\nYour task is to:\\n- Analyze a user objective\\n- Break it into atomic executable subtasks\\n- Each subtask should represent ONE specialized operation\\n- Keep subtasks concise and action-oriented\\n\\nReturn the output as a Python list of strings.\\n\\nExample:\\n[\\n    \\\"Analyze the job description\\\",\\n    \\\"Analyze the candidate resume\\\",\\n    \\\"Conduct technical interview\\\",\\n    \\\"Send emails as and when needed\\\",\\n    \\\"Score candidate responses\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate final evaluation report\\\"\\n]\\n\\n\\n---\\n# **Context from Upstream Tasks**\\nNo completed previous tasks context available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task2:\\n  Objective: Decompose each actionable component into specialized atomic subtasks\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nParse the high-level user objective into core actionable components\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```python\\n[\\n    \\\"Receive the user's high-level objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Interpret the objective details\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify the desired workflow outcome\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract key entities mentioned in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Extract required resources specified by the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Detect implicit assumptions in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Identify explicit constraints in the objective\\\",\\n    \\\"Define the workflow's scope\\\",\\n    \\\"Outline the workflow's boundaries\\\",\\n    \\\"Outline major workflow phases\\\",\\n    \\\"Prioritize each phase based on dependencies\\\",\\n    \\\"Sequence phases in logical order\\\",\\n    \\\"Generate and send clarification questions for ambiguities\\\"\\n]\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-26T17:30:40.353107\"\n}"}
